{"title_page": "Serbia at the EuroBasket 2021 qualification", "text_new": "{{main|Serbia national basketball team}}\n{{Infobox basketball club season\n|club               = Serbia\n|updated            = {{dts|2020|2|22}}\n|image              = \n|image_size         = \n|alt                = \n|caption            = \n|chrtitle           = President\n|chairman           = [[Predrag Danilovi\u0107]]\n|manager            = [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]]\n|stadium            = [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]]\n|league             = Qualifiers\n|league result      = ''[[EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group E|In progress]]''\n|PIR_leader         = \n|pir                = \n|top_scorer         = \n|ppg                = \n|rebounds_leader    = \n|rpg                = \n|assists_leader     = \n|apg                = \n|highest attendance = \n|lowest attendance  = \n|average attendance = \n|largest win        = {{Nowrap|80\u201358 {{nbt|Finland}} }}<br><small>(20 February 2020)</small>\n|largest loss       = {{Nowrap|90\u201394 {{nbt|Georgia}} }}<br><small>(23 February 2020)</small>\n}}\nThe '''Serbia team for EuroBasket 2021 qualification''' represents [[Serbia national basketball team|Serbia]] at the [[EuroBasket 2021 qualification]]. The team has been coached by [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]], with assistant coaches [[Dejan Milojevi\u0107]], [[Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107]], and [[Jovica Antoni\u0107]]. The team plays their home games at the [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]] in [[Belgrade]].\n\nAs a participant in the second round of the [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup qualification (Europe)|2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup qualification]], Serbia was qualified for the second stage of the EuroBasket 2021 qualification.\n\n==Timeline==\n{{also|2020 Serbia men's OQT basketball team}}\n* '''27 January 2020''': Coaching and team staff announced\n* '''11 February 2020''': 15-man first window roster announced<ref>{{cite web |title=Teodosic, Raduljica headline Serbia squad for February Qualifiers |url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/news/teodosic-raduljica-headline-serbia-squad-for-february-qualifiers |website=fiba.basketball |accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n* '''20\u201323 February 2020''': The first window\n* '''27\u201330 November 2020''': The second window\n* '''18\u201321 February 2021''': The third window\n\n==Roster==\nOn 11 February 2020, head coach [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]] announced a 15-man roster for first window games against {{nbt|Finland}} on 20 February and {{nbt|Georgia}} on 23 February.<ref>{{cite web |title=Koko\u0161kov odabrao igra\u010de za kvalifikacije za Evrobasket |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=11&nav_id=1653257 |website=b92.net |accessdate=11 February 2020|language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Selektor Koko\u0161kov odredio spisak A reprezentacije za februarski FIBA \u201eprozor\u201c |url=http://www.kss.rs/selektor-kokoskov-odredio-spisak-a-reprezentacije-za-februarski-fiba-prozor/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=11 February 2020|language=Serbian}}</ref> Center [[Miroslav Raduljica]] and forward [[Marko Simonovi\u0107 (born 1986)|Marko Simonovi\u0107]] are the only members of [[2019 Serbia FIBA Basketball World Cup team|Serbia roster at the 2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup]] included into the February roster. On 17 February, guard [[Luka A\u0161\u0107eri\u0107]] was added to the roster due to an injury of the guard [[Ognjen Dobri\u0107]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pozvan A\u0161\u0107eri\u0107 u reprezentaciju umesto povre\u0111enog Dobri\u0107a |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=17&nav_id=1655741 |website=b92.net |accessdate=18 February 2020}}</ref> Even he was shortlisted, guard [[Milo\u0161 Teodosi\u0107]] wasn't added to the roster due to a demand of his club [[Virtus Bologna]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Virtus tra\u017ei kompletno osiguranje za Teodosi\u0107a |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=18&nav_id=1656046 |website=b92.net |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bez Teodosi\u0107a i protiv Gruzije |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=20&nav_id=1656859 |website=b92.net |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> Guards [[Nikola Rebi\u0107]] and [[Uro\u0161 Trifunovi\u0107]], forwards [[Dalibor Ili\u0107]] and [[Stefan \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107 (basketball)|Stefan \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107]], and center [[Dejan Kravi\u0107]] made senior debut with the Serbian national team.\n\nThe following is the Serbia roster for the first window.\n{{FIBA roster header|team=Serbia national basketball team \u2013 EuroBasket 2021 qualification\n| color1 = White| bg1 = #006CB7| color2 = White| bg2 = #D93943}}\n<!-- list of players -->\n{{FIBA player | num = 4 | first = Milo\u0161 | last = Teodosi\u0107 | pos = PG | m = 1.96 | year = 1987 | month = 3 | date = 19 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[Virtus Bologna]] | nat = ITA |note= }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 5 | first = Marko | last = Simonovi\u0107 | dab=born 1986 | pos = SF | m = 2.03 | year = 1986 | month = 5 | date = 30 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Cedevita Olimpija|Cedevita Olimpija]] | nat = SLO}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 6  | first = Aleksa | last = Radanov | pos = SG | m = 2.02 | year = 1998 | month = 2 | date = 1 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK FMP|FMP]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 10 | first = Ognjen | last = Jaramaz | pos = PG | m = 1.93 | year = 1995 | month = 1 | date = 9 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 11 | first = Dejan | last = Kravi\u0107 | pos = C | m = 2.13 | year = 1990 | month = 9 | date = 9 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[Obradoiro CAB|Obradoiro]] | nat = SPA}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 12 | first = Novica | last = Veli\u010dkovi\u0107 | pos = PF | m = 2.05 | year = 1986 | month = 10 | date = 5 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 13 | first = Miroslav | last = Raduljica | pos = C | m = 2.13 | year = 1988 | month = 1 | date = 5 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[Jiangsu Dragons]] | nat = CHN |note=C}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 20 | first = Dejan | last = Todorovi\u0107 | pos = SF | m = 1.96 | year = 1994 | month = 5 | date = 29 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[BC Andorra|Andorra]] | nat = ESP }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 22 | first = Dalibor | last = Ili\u0107 | pos = SF | m = 2.06 | year = 2000 | month = 3 | date = 4 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Igokea|Igokea]] | nat = BIH}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 25 | first = Rade | last = Zagorac | pos = SF | m = 2.05 | year = 1995 | month = 8 | date = 12 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 30 | first = Aleksa | last = Avramovi\u0107 | pos = PG | m = 1.92 | year = 1994 | month = 10 | date = 25 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[CB Estudiantes|Estudiantes]] | nat = SPA}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 31 | first = Ognjen | last = Dobri\u0107 | pos = SG | m = 1.98 | year = 1994 | month = 10 | date = 27 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda]] | nat = SRB |inj=}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 32 | first = Uro\u0161 | last = Trifunovi\u0107 | pos = SG | m = 1.99 | year = 2000 | month = 12 | date = 5 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 44 | first = Nikola | last = Rebi\u0107 | pos = PG | m = 1.88 | year = 1995 | month = 1 | date = 22 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[BC Enisey|Enisey]] | nat = RUS }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 45 | first = Stefan | last = \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107 | dab=basketball | pos = PF | m = 2.06 | year = 1998 | month = 12 | date = 4 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK FMP|FMP]] | nat = SRB |note=}}\n{{FIBA player | num =  | first = Luka | last = A\u0161\u0107eri\u0107 | pos = G | m = 2.01 | year = 1997 | month = 1 | date = 10 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Mega Basket|Mega Bemax]] | nat = SRB |note=}}\n<!-- end list of players -->\n{{FIBA roster footer\n| head_coach = \n* {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]]\n| asst_coach = \n* {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Jovica Antoni\u0107]]\n* {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Dejan Milojevi\u0107]]\n* {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107]]\n| otherlegend = \n* '''(C)''' Team captain\n* '''(X)''' Unavailable for<br />the upcoming game\n* '''Club''' \u2013 describes club<br />on 20 February 2020\n* '''Age''' \u2013 describes age<br>on 20 February 2020\n}}\n\n=== Depth chart===\n<!--Selected players (12/?) with ? or more games played. Number in parentheses indicates how many times player was in a starting line-up. -->\n{{Basketball depth chart\n |line_color  = 006CB7\n |alt_color   = D93943\n |starter_c   = [[Miroslav Raduljica]]\n |starter_pf  = [[Marko Simonovi\u0107 (born 1986)|Marko Simonovi\u0107]]\n |starter_sf  = [[Dejan Todorovi\u0107]]\n |starter_sg  = [[Ognjen Jaramaz]]\n |starter_pg  = [[Nikola Rebi\u0107]]\n\n |bench 1_c   = [[Dejan Kravi\u0107]]\n |bench 1_pf  = [[Novica Veli\u010dkovi\u0107]]\n |bench 1_sf  = [[Rade Zagorac]]\n |bench 1_sg  = [[Aleksa Radanov]]\n |bench 1_pg  = [[Aleksa Avramovi\u0107]]\n\n |bench 2_c   = \n |bench 2_pf  = \n |bench 2_sf  = [[Dalibor Ili\u0107]]\n |bench 2_sg  = [[Uro\u0161 Trifunovi\u0107]]\n |bench 2_pg  = \n }}\n\n== Staff ==\nAt the end of the [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup]] where Serbia won 5th place, head coach [[Aleksandar \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107]] announced his decision to leave the position after six years.<ref>{{cite news |last1=T. |first1=P. |title=\u0110or\u0111evi\u0107 vi\u0161e nije selektor Srbije! |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kina2019/vesti.php?nav_id=1591234 |accessdate=14 September 2019 |work=b92.net |date=14 September 2019 |language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0110OR\u0110EVI\u0106 VI\u0160E NIJE SELEKTOR SRBIJE: Znam kad treba da odem |url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.295.html:818318-DjORDjEVIC-VISE-NIJE-SELEKTOR-SRBIJE-Znam-kad-treba-da-odem-VIDEO |website=novosti.rs |accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref> On 20 November 2019, the [[Basketball Federation of Serbia]] named [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]] the new head coach of the Serbia team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Igor Koko\u0161kov novi selektor Srbije! |url=http://www.kss.rs/igor-kokoskov-novi-selektor-srbije/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref> In December, [[Dejan Milojevi\u0107]] and [[Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107]] were named assistant coaches.<ref>{{cite web |title=SK: Milojevi\u0107 i Jovanovi\u0107 pomo\u0107nici Koko\u0161kovu! |url=http://sportklub.rs/Kosarka/Reprezentacija/a316629-SK-Milojevic-i-Jovanovic-pomocnici-Kokoskovu.html |website=sportklub.rs |accessdate=6 December 2019}}</ref> On 27 January, coach Koko\u0161kov announced the full staff.<ref>{{cite web |title=Selektor Koko\u0161kov odredio sastav stru\u010dnog \u0161taba seniorske reprezentacije |url=http://www.kss.rs/selektor-kokoskov-odredio-sastav-strucnog-staba-seniorske-reprezentacije/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"140px\"| Position\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"180px\"| Staff member\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"40px\" | Age\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"180px\"| Team\n|-\n| '''[[Coach (basketball)|Head coach]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Igor|Koko\u0161kov}} || {{age|1971|12|17|2020|02|20}}  || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sacramento Kings]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|'''Assistant coaches''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Jovica|Antoni\u0107}} || {{age|1966|7|13|2020|02|20}} || {{N/A}}\n|- \n| {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Dejan|Milojevi\u0107}} || {{age|1977|4|15|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Mega Basket|Mega Bemax]]\n|- \n| {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Vladimir|Jovanovi\u0107|dab=basketball}} || {{age|1984|3|15|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK FMP|FMP]]\n|-\n| rowspan=1| '''[[Conditioning coach]]''' ||  {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Vladimir|Koprivica}} || {{age|1952|12|5|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Partizan|Partizan NIS]]\n|-\n| '''[[Scout (sport)|Scout]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Bogdan|Karai\u010di\u0107}} || {{age|1984|7|31|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[PBC Lokomotiv Kuban|Lokomotiv Kuban]]\n|-\n| '''Team manager''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Neboj\u0161a|Ili\u0107|dab=basketball}} || {{age|1968|2|26|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda mts]]\n|-\n| '''[[Physician]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Milan|Mirkovi\u0107|dab=physician|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|'''[[Physiotherapist]]s''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Du\u0161an|Saji\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n|  {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Velibor|Kosanovi\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| '''[[Equipment manager]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Jovica|Ani\u010di\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n|}\n<small>'''Age''' \u2013 describes age on 20 February 2020</small>\n\n<small>Source: [http://www.kss.rs/muske-reprezentacije/seniori/2020-2/?langcir=lat KSS]</small>\n\n==Uniform==\n{{columns-start|num=2}}\n*'''Supplier:''' [[Peak Sport Products|Peak]]\n*'''Main sponsor:''' [[Ganten]]\n*'''Back sponsor:''' [[Zavarovalnica Triglav|Triglav]] <small>(below [[Number (sports)#Basketball|number]])</small>\n*'''Shorts sponsor:''' [[Mobile Telephony of Serbia|mts]]\n{{column}}\n{| border=\"0\"\n|{{Basketball kit\n| title       = [[Basketball uniform|Home]]\n| body        = FFFFFF\n| pattern_b   = \n| shorts      = FFFFFF\n| pattern_s   = \n}}\n|{{Basketball kit\n| title       = [[Basketball uniform|Away]]\n| body        = 0000aa\n| pattern_b   = \n| shorts      = 0000aa\n| pattern_s   = \n}}\n|}\n{{columns-end}}\n\n== Qualification ==\n{{Further|EuroBasket 2021 qualification}}\nThe draw was held on 22 July 2019 in [[Munich]], Germany. Serbia was drawn into Group E with [[Finland national basketball team|Finland]], [[Georgia national basketball team|Georgia]], and the [[EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group H|Pre-Qualifiers Group H]] winner.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/news/draw-results-in-for-fiba-eurobasket-2021-qualifiers|title=Draw results in for FIBA EuroBasket 2021 Qualifiers|publisher=[[FIBA]]|date=14 August 2019|accessdate=23 July 2017}}</ref> These matches will be played in three windows from 17 to 25 February 2020; from 23 November to 1 December 2020 and from 15 to 23 February 2021 with two games played by each team in every window.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/europeanqualifiers/eng.pdf|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=14 August 2019|title=Road to World Cup 2019 and EuroBasket 2021}}</ref>\n\nGroup E is one of eight qualifiers groups of four teams. The groups will be conducted in a [[Round-robin tournament|round-robin system]], with each team playing all other teams in the respective group in home and away games. Georgia as the host and the two other highest placed teams will qualify for the [[EuroBasket 2021]].<ref name=seed2019>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/news/seedings-confirmed-ahead-of-fiba-eurobasket-2021-qualifiers-draw|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=14 August 2019|title=Seedings confirmed ahead of FIBA EuroBasket 2021 Qualifiers Draw}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 August, [[Switzerland national basketball team|Switzerland]] won Pre-Qualifiers Group H and advance to the next round joining Serbia and others in Group E.<ref>{{cite web |title=Srbija je dobila poslednjeg protivnika \u2013 \u0160vajcarsku |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2019&mm=08&dd=21&nav_id=1580743 |website=b92.net |accessdate=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Group E ===\n{{main|EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group E 2|l1=Group E}}\n{{#section:EuroBasket 2021 qualification|Group E}}\n\n====Finland (Away game)====\n{{basketballbox|bg=#eee|date=20 February 2020 |time=19:00 ([[Eastern European Time|EET]]) |place= [[Espoo Metro Areena]], [[Espoo]]\n|teamA = {{bk-rt|FIN}} |scoreA = 58\n|teamB = '''{{bk|SRB}}''' |scoreB =  '''80'''\n| Q1 = 10\u2013'''19''' | Q2 = 14\u2013'''18''' | Q3 = 13\u2013'''23''' | Q4 = '''21'''\u201320\n|report = [http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/game/2002/Finland-Serbia Boxscore]\n|points1 = [[Topias Palmi|Palmi]] 16\n|rebounds1 = [[Tuukka Kotti|Kotti]] 6\n|assist1 = ''three players'' 3\n|points2 = [[Miroslav Raduljica|Raduljica]] 19\n|rebounds2 = ''three players'' 8\n|assist2 = ''four players'' 3\n| attendance = \n| referee = Yohan Rosso (FRA), Tolga Sahin (ITA), Andrei Sharapa (BLR)\n| TV=[[RTS1 (Serbian TV channel)|RTS1]]\n}}\n\n====Georgia (Home game)====\n{{basketballbox|bg=#eee|date=23 February 2020 |time=17:00 ([[Central European Time|CET]]) |place= [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]], [[Belgrade]]\n|teamA = {{bk-rt|SRB}} |scoreA = 90\n|teamB = '''{{bk|GEO}}''' |scoreB = '''94'''\n|Q1 = '''28'''\u201318 |Q2 = 20\u2013'''23''' |Q3 = 19\u2013'''24''' |Q4 = 23\u2013'''29'''\n|report =[http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/game/2302/Serbia-Georgia Boxscore] \n|points1 = [[Aleksa Avramovi\u0107|Avramovi\u0107]] 27\n|rebounds1 = [[Miroslav Raduljica|Raduljica]], [[Rade Zagorac|Zagorac]] 5\n|assist1 = [[Ognjen Jaramaz|Jaramaz]] 6\n|points2 = [[Thad McFadden (basketball)|McFadden]] 33\n|rebounds2 = [[Giorgi Shermadini|Shermadini]] 11\n|assist2 = [[Thad McFadden (basketball)|McFadden]] 7\n|referee = Antonio Conde (ESP), Carsten Straub