 = \n|caption            = \n|chrtitle           = President\n|chairman           = [[Predrag Danilovi\u0107]]\n|manager            = [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]]\n|stadium            = [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]]\n|league             = Qualifiers\n|league result      = ''[[EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group E|In progress]]''\n|PIR_leader         = \n|pir                = \n|top_scorer         = \n|ppg                = \n|rebounds_leader    = \n|rpg                = \n|assists_leader     = \n|apg                = \n|highest attendance = \n|lowest attendance  = \n|average attendance = \n|largest win        = {{Nowrap|80\u201358 {{nbt|Finland}} }}<br><small>(20 February 2020)</small>\n|largest loss       = {{Nowrap|90\u201394 {{nbt|Georgia}} }}<br><small>(23 February 2020)</small>\n}}\nThe '''Serbia team for EuroBasket 2021 qualification''' represents [[Serbia national basketball team|Serbia]] at the [[EuroBasket 2021 qualification]]. The team has been coached by [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]], with assistant coaches [[Dejan Milojevi\u0107]], [[Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107]], and [[Jovica Antoni\u0107]]. The team plays their home games at the [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]] in [[Belgrade]].\n\nAs a participant in the second round of the [[2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup qualification (Europe)|2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup qualification]], Serbia was qualified for the second stage of the EuroBasket 2021 qualification.\n\n==Timeline==\n{{also|2020 Serbia men's OQT basketball team}}\n* '''27 January 2020''': Coaching and team staff announced\n* '''11 February 2020''': 15-man first window roster announced<ref>{{cite web |title=Teodosic, Raduljica headline Serbia squad for February Qualifiers |url=http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/news/teodosic-raduljica-headline-serbia-squad-for-february-qualifiers |website=fiba.basketball |accessdate=11 February 2020}}</ref>\n* '''20\u201323 February 2020''': The first window\n* '''27\u201330 November 2020''': The second window\n* '''18\u201321 February 2021''': The third window\n\n==Roster==\nOn 11 February 2020, head coach [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]] announced a 15-man roster for first window games against {{nbt|Finland}} on 20 February and {{nbt|Georgia}} on 23 February.<ref>{{cite web |title=Koko\u0161kov odabrao igra\u010de za kvalifikacije za Evrobasket |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=11&nav_id=1653257 |website=b92.net |accessdate=11 February 2020|language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Selektor Koko\u0161kov odredio spisak A reprezentacije za februarski FIBA \u201eprozor\u201c |url=http://www.kss.rs/selektor-kokoskov-odredio-spisak-a-reprezentacije-za-februarski-fiba-prozor/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=11 February 2020|language=Serbian}}</ref> Center [[Miroslav Raduljica]] and forward [[Marko Simonovi\u0107 (born 1986)|Marko Simonovi\u0107]] are the only members of [[2019 Serbia FIBA Basketball World Cup team|Serbia roster at the 2019 FIBA Basketball World Cup]] included into the February roster. On 17 February, guard [[Luka A\u0161\u0107eri\u0107]] was added to the roster due to an injury of the guard [[Ognjen Dobri\u0107]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Pozvan A\u0161\u0107eri\u0107 u reprezentaciju umesto povre\u0111enog Dobri\u0107a |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=17&nav_id=1655741 |website=b92.net |accessdate=18 February 2020}}</ref> Even he was shortlisted, guard [[Milo\u0161 Teodosi\u0107]] wasn't added to the roster due to a demand of his club [[Virtus Bologna]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Virtus tra\u017ei kompletno osiguranje za Teodosi\u0107a |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=18&nav_id=1656046 |website=b92.net |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Bez Teodosi\u0107a i protiv Gruzije |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2020&mm=02&dd=20&nav_id=1656859 |website=b92.net |accessdate=20 February 2020}}</ref> Guards [[Nikola Rebi\u0107]] and [[Uro\u0161 Trifunovi\u0107]], forwards [[Dalibor Ili\u0107]] and [[Stefan \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107 (basketball)|Stefan \u0110or\u0111evi\u0107]], and center [[Dejan Kravi\u0107]] made senior debut with the Serbian national team.\n\nThe following is the Serbia roster for the first window.\n{{FIBA roster header|team=Serbia national basketball team \u2013 EuroBasket 2021 qualification\n| color1 = White| bg1 = #006CB7| color2 = White| bg2 = #D93943}}\n<!-- list of players -->\n{{FIBA player | num = 4 | first = Milo\u0161 | last = Teodosi\u0107 | pos = PG | m = 1.96 | year = 1987 | month = 3 | date = 19 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[Virtus Bologna]] | nat = ITA |note= }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 5 | first = Marko | last = Simonovi\u0107 | dab=born 1986 | pos = SF | m = 2.03 | year = 1986 | month = 5 | date = 30 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Cedevita Olimpija|Cedevita Olimpija]] | nat = SLO}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 6  | first = Aleksa | last = Radanov | pos = SG | m = 2.02 | year = 1998 | month = 2 | date = 1 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK FMP|FMP]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 10 | first = Ognjen | last = Jaramaz | pos = PG | m = 1.93 | year = 1995 | month = 1 | date = 9 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 11 | first = Dejan | last = Kravi\u0107 | pos = C | m = 2.13 | year = 1990 | month = 9 | date = 9 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[Obradoiro CAB|Obradoiro]] | nat = SPA}}\n{{FIBA player | num = 12 | first = Novica | last = Veli\u010dkovi\u0107 | pos = PF | m = 2.05 | year = 1986 | month = 10 | date = 5 | compyear = 2020 | compmonth = 2 | compdate = 20 | clublink = [[KK Partizan|Partizan]] | nat = SRB }}\n{{FIBA player | num = 13 | first = Miroslav | last = Raduljica | pos = C | m = 2.13 | yea