date=14 September 2019 |language=Serbian}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\u0110OR\u0110EVI\u0106 VI\u0160E NIJE SELEKTOR SRBIJE: Znam kad treba da odem |url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/sport.295.html:818318-DjORDjEVIC-VISE-NIJE-SELEKTOR-SRBIJE-Znam-kad-treba-da-odem-VIDEO |website=novosti.rs |accessdate=14 September 2019}}</ref> On 20 November 2019, the [[Basketball Federation of Serbia]] named [[Igor Koko\u0161kov]] the new head coach of the Serbia team.<ref>{{cite web |title=Igor Koko\u0161kov novi selektor Srbije! |url=http://www.kss.rs/igor-kokoskov-novi-selektor-srbije/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=21 November 2019}}</ref> In December, [[Dejan Milojevi\u0107]] and [[Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107 (basketball)|Vladimir Jovanovi\u0107]] were named assistant coaches.<ref>{{cite web |title=SK: Milojevi\u0107 i Jovanovi\u0107 pomo\u0107nici Koko\u0161kovu! |url=http://sportklub.rs/Kosarka/Reprezentacija/a316629-SK-Milojevic-i-Jovanovic-pomocnici-Kokoskovu.html |website=sportklub.rs |accessdate=6 December 2019}}</ref> On 27 January, coach Koko\u0161kov announced the full staff.<ref>{{cite web |title=Selektor Koko\u0161kov odredio sastav stru\u010dnog \u0161taba seniorske reprezentacije |url=http://www.kss.rs/selektor-kokoskov-odredio-sastav-strucnog-staba-seniorske-reprezentacije/?langcir=lat |website=kss.rs |accessdate=27 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:95%\"\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"140px\"| Position\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"180px\"| Staff member\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"40px\" | Age\n!scope=\"col\" width=\"180px\"| Team\n|-\n| '''[[Coach (basketball)|Head coach]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Igor|Koko\u0161kov}} || {{age|1971|12|17|2020|02|20}}  || {{flagicon|USA}} [[Sacramento Kings]]\n|-\n| rowspan=3|'''Assistant coaches''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Jovica|Antoni\u0107}} || {{age|1966|7|13|2020|02|20}} || {{N/A}}\n|- \n| {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Dejan|Milojevi\u0107}} || {{age|1977|4|15|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Mega Basket|Mega Bemax]]\n|- \n| {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Vladimir|Jovanovi\u0107|dab=basketball}} || {{age|1984|3|15|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK FMP|FMP]]\n|-\n| rowspan=1| '''[[Conditioning coach]]''' ||  {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Vladimir|Koprivica}} || {{age|1952|12|5|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Partizan|Partizan NIS]]\n|-\n| '''[[Scout (sport)|Scout]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Bogdan|Karai\u010di\u0107}} || {{age|1984|7|31|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|RUS}} [[PBC Lokomotiv Kuban|Lokomotiv Kuban]]\n|-\n| '''Team manager''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Neboj\u0161a|Ili\u0107|dab=basketball}} || {{age|1968|2|26|2020|02|20}} || {{flagicon|SRB}} [[KK Crvena zvezda|Crvena zvezda mts]]\n|-\n| '''[[Physician]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Milan|Mirkovi\u0107|dab=physician|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| rowspan=2|'''[[Physiotherapist]]s''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Du\u0161an|Saji\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n|  {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Velibor|Kosanovi\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n| '''[[Equipment manager]]''' || {{flagicon|SRB}} {{sortname|Jovica|Ani\u010di\u0107|nolink=1}} ||{{N/A}} || {{N/A}}\n|-\n|}\n<small>'''Age''' \u2013 describes age on 20 February 2020</small>\n\n<small>Source: [http://www.kss.rs/muske-reprezentacije/seniori/2020-2/?langcir=lat KSS]</small>\n\n==Uniform==\n{{columns-start|num=2}}\n*'''Supplier:''' [[Peak Sport Products|Peak]]\n*'''Main sponsor:''' [[Ganten]]\n*'''Back sponsor:''' [[Zavarovalnica Triglav|Triglav]] <small>(below [[Number (sports)#Basketball|number]])</small>\n*'''Shorts sponsor:''' [[Mobile Telephony of Serbia|mts]]\n{{column}}\n{| border=\"0\"\n|{{Basketball kit\n| title       = [[Basketball uniform|Home]]\n| body        = FFFFFF\n| pattern_b   = \n| shorts      = FFFFFF\n| pattern_s   = \n}}\n|{{Basketball kit\n| title       = [[Basketball uniform|Away]]\n| body        = 0000aa\n| pattern_b   = \n| shorts      = 0000aa\n| pattern_s   = \n}}\n|}\n{{columns-end}}\n\n== Qualification ==\n{{Further|EuroBasket 2021 qualification}}\nThe draw was held on 22 July 2019 in [[Munich]], Germany. Serbia was drawn into Group E with [[Finland national basketball team|Finland]], [[Georgia national basketball team|Georgia]], and the [[EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group H|Pre-Qualifiers Group H]] winner.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/news/draw-results-in-for-fiba-eurobasket-2021-qualifiers|title=Draw results in for FIBA EuroBasket 2021 Qualifiers|publisher=[[FIBA]]|date=14 August 2019|accessdate=23 July 2017}}</ref> These matches will be played in three windows from 17 to 25 February 2020; from 23 November to 1 December 2020 and from 15 to 23 February 2021 with two games played by each team in every window.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/europeanqualifiers/eng.pdf|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=14 August 2019|title=Road to World Cup 2019 and EuroBasket 2021}}</ref>\n\nGroup E is one of eight qualifiers groups of four teams. The groups will be conducted in a [[Round-robin tournament|round-robin system]], with each team playing all other teams in the respective group in home and away games. Georgia as the host and the two other highest placed teams will qualify for the [[EuroBasket 2021]].<ref name=seed2019>{{cite web|url=http://www.fiba.basketball/news/seedings-confirmed-ahead-of-fiba-eurobasket-2021-qualifiers-draw|publisher=FIBA|accessdate=14 August 2019|title=Seedings confirmed ahead of FIBA EuroBasket 2021 Qualifiers Draw}}</ref>\n\nOn 21 August, [[Switzerland national basketball team|Switzerland]] won Pre-Qualifiers Group H and advance to the next round joining Serbia and others in Group E.<ref>{{cite web |title=Srbija je dobila poslednjeg protivnika \u2013 \u0160vajcarsku |url=https://www.b92.net/sport/kosarka/vesti.php?yyyy=2019&mm=08&dd=21&nav_id=1580743 |website=b92.net |accessdate=22 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Group E ===\n{{main|EuroBasket 2021 qualification#Group E 2|l1=Group E}}\n{{#section:EuroBasket 2021 qualification|Group E}}\n\n====Finland (Away game)====\n{{basketballbox|bg=#eee|date=20 February 2020 |time=19:00 ([[Eastern European Time|EET]]) |place= [[Espoo Metro Areena]], [[Espoo]]\n|teamA = {{bk-rt|FIN}} |scoreA = 58\n|teamB = '''{{bk|SRB}}''' |scoreB =  '''80'''\n| Q1 = 10\u2013'''19''' | Q2 = 14\u2013'''18''' | Q3 = 13\u2013'''23''' | Q4 = '''21'''\u201320\n|report = [http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/game/2002/Finland-Serbia Boxscore]\n|points1 = [[Topias Palmi|Palmi]] 16\n|rebounds1 = [[Tuukka Kotti|Kotti]] 6\n|assist1 = ''three players'' 3\n|points2 = [[Miroslav Raduljica|Raduljica]] 19\n|rebounds2 = ''three players'' 8\n|assist2 = ''four players'' 3\n| attendance = \n| referee = Yohan Rosso (FRA), Tolga Sahin (ITA), Andrei Sharapa (BLR)\n| TV=[[RTS1 (Serbian TV channel)|RTS1]]\n}}\n\n====Georgia (Home game)====\n{{basketballbox|bg=#eee|date=23 February 2020 |time=17:00 ([[Central European Time|CET]]) |place= [[Aleksandar Nikoli\u0107 Hall]], [[Belgrade]]\n|teamA = {{bk-rt|SRB}} |scoreA = 90\n|teamB = '''{{bk|GEO}}''' |scoreB = '''94'''\n|Q1 = '''28'''\u201318 |Q2 = 20\u2013'''23''' |Q3 = 19\u2013'''24''' |Q4 = 23\u2013'''29'''\n|report =[http://www.fiba.basketball/eurobasket/2021/qualifiers/game/2302/Serbia-Georgia Boxscore] \n|points1 = [[Aleksa Avramovi\u0107|Avramovi\u0107]] 27\n|rebounds1 = [[Miroslav Raduljica|Raduljica]], [[Rade Zagorac|Zagorac]] 5\n|assist1 = [[Ognjen Jaramaz|Jaramaz]] 6\n|points2 = [[Thad McFadden (basketball)|McFadden]] 33\n|rebounds2 = [[Giorgi Shermadini|Shermadini]] 11\n|assist2 = [[Thad McFadden (basketball)|McFadden]] 7\n|referee = Antonio Conde (ESP), Carsten Straube (GER), Luis Castillo (ESP)\n|attendance= 5,000\n| TV=[[RTS1 (Serbian TV channel)|RTS1]]\n}}\n\n====Switzerland (Away game) ====\n{{basketballbox|bg=#eee|date=27 November 2020 |time= |place= \n|id = \n|teamA = {{bk-rt|SUI}} |scoreA = \n|teamB = {{bk|SRB}} |scoreB = \n|Q1 = |Q2 = |Q3 =