cessdate=24 September 2013}}</ref> He won all 100\u2013800 m events at the 2013, 2015 and 2017 world championships.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/events/lyon-2013/live-results Lyon 2013 Live Results], IPC Athletics World Championships, 19\u201328 July</ref> At the 2012 and 2016 Paralympics he won three gold and one silver medal.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.london2012.com/paralympics/athlete/ktila-walid-5501096/events |title=Walid Ktila \u2013 Events and results |publisher=London 2012 |accessdate=10 September 2012}}</ref><ref>[https://www.rio2016.com/en/paralympics/athlete/walid-ktila Walid Ktila]. rio2016.com</ref>\n\n==World records==\nWalid holds two [[List of IPC world records in athletics|IPC world records in athletics]] in 100 m and 200 m T34 events.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\"\n|-\n! Event\n! Record\n! Competition\n! Location\n! Date\n|-\n| 100 m\n| 15.69 (+0.1&nbsp;m/s)\n|\n| [[Kuwait City]], Kuwait\n| 17 January 2012\n|-\n| 200 m\n| 27.98 (\u22120.3&nbsp;m/s)\n| [[Athletics at the 2012 Summer Paralympics|Paralympic Games]]\n| [[London]], Great Britain\n| 4 September 2012\n|}\n\n== See also==\n* [[Tunisia at the 2013 IPC Athletics World Championships]]\n* [[Tunisia at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n* [[Tunisia at the Paralympics]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Walid Ktila}}\n* {{IPC athlete|id=walid-ktila|old_id=966512}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ktila, Walid}}\n[[Category:1985 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tunisian male athletes]]\n[[Category:Tunisian wheelchair racers]]\n[[Category:Male wheelchair racers]]\n[[Category:Paralympic athletes of Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic gold medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Paralympic silver medalists for Tunisia]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Athletes (track and field) at the 2016 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2012 Summer Paralympics]]\n[[Category:Meda